    "body": "### Problem\n\nAfter https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/28b7c2df521744347e3286927af13fd8421f0ea1 (found with bisect) the hover preview window does not close when `:edit`'ing another file, even when you move the cursor\n\n<details>\n\n<summary>init.lua video</summary>\n\nhttps://github.com/user-attachments/assets/ee97ab6b-a538-48b7-b548-30d8caecd14e\n\n</details>\n\n\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nReproduce with this init.lua, have to have gopls on your path.\n\n\n\n```lua\nvim.lsp.config(\"gopls\", {\n\tcmd = { \"gopls\" },\n\tfiletypes = { \"go\", \"gomod\", \"gowork\", \"gotmpl\" },\n})\nvim.lsp.enable(\"gopls\")\n\nlocal file1 = [[\n    package main\n\n    func main() {\n        other()\n    }\n]]\n\nlocal file2 = [[\n    package main\n    func other() {\n\n    }\n]]\n\nvim.fn.writefile(vim.split(file1, \"\\n\"), \"file1.go\")\nvim.fn.writefile(vim.split(file2, \"\\n\"), \"file2.go\")\n\nvim.cmd.edit(\"file1.go\")\nvim.cmd(\"set filetype=go\")\n\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nIt should close like the way it did before 28b7c2df521744347e3286927af13fd8421f0ea1\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux/mac\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew/archlinux",
